### JWT Token Operations Testing
### Test token validation, refresh, and protected endpoints

# Variables (Update these after successful login)
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7249@accessToken = YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@refreshToken = YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Test Token Validation
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/validate
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 2. Test Get Current User (Protected Endpoint)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 3. Test Refresh Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### 4. Test Protected Endpoint Without Token (Should Fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me

### 5. Test Protected Endpoint With Invalid Token (Should Fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_here

### 6. Test Protected Endpoint With Expired Token (Should Fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.expired_token

### 7. Test Refresh With Invalid Token (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "invalid_refresh_token"
}

### 8. Test Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}",
  "logoutFromAllDevices": false
}

### 9. Test Logout From All Devices
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}",
  "logoutFromAllDevices": true
}